'''''Cosmic Conflict''''' (stylized as '''''Cosmic Conflict!''''') first person space [[shoot 'em up]] and the [[List of Videopac games|11th official game]] released in 1978 for the [[Philips]] [[Magnavox Odyssey²|Videopac]] console (known as [[Magnavox Odyssey²]] in the [[United States]]). The player is  a commander of the Centurion, an Earth Federation starship that guards a remote corner of the galaxy and defend against the alien invasion fleet trying to enslave Earth.

==Gameplay==
[[File:Cosmicconflict2.jpg|thumb]]

''Cosmic Conflict'' is a 2D shoot 'em up played from a first-person perspective. It is set in outer space with colorful planets in the background. The player must travel within the Centurion and shoot different enemies. The player's score depends upon how many enemies the player is able to shoot.

==Reception==
In the "Arcade Alley" column of ''[[Video (magazine)|Video]]'' magazine it was praised as "a classic space battle that brings the flavor of ''[[Star Wars]]'' to the home screen".<ref name=kunkel>{{cite journal |last1= Kunkel |first1= Bill |author-link1= Bill Kunkel (gaming)|last2= Laney |first2= Frank T. II|author-link2= Arnie Katz|date= January 1980 |title= Arcade Alley: Magnavox Odyssey² |journal= [[Video (magazine)|Video]]|publisher= Reese Communications|volume= 3|issue= 3|pages= 72, 73, and 84 |issn= 0147-8907}}</ref>{{rp|84}}

